import java.util.*;
import java.io.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int k = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        int[] colors = new int[k];
        for (int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
            colors[i] = i + 1;
        }
        boolean isValid = true;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < k; j++) {
                if (a[i] == colors[j]) {
                    isValid = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (!isValid) {
                break;
            }
        }
        if (isValid) {
            System.out.println("YES");
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                System.out.print(colors[a[i] - 1] + " ");
            }
            System.out.println();
        } else {
            System.out.println("NO");
        }
    }
}

    scanf("%d", &n);
    for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        scanf("%d", &a[i]);
    }
    for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
            lcm = a[i] * a[j] / gcd(a[i], a[j]);
            if (lcm < min_lcm) {
                min_lcm = lcm;
                i = i;
                j = j;
            }
        }
    }
    printf("%d %d\n", i + 1, j + 1);
    return 0;
}

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);
        int t = in.nextInt();
        while(t-->0){
            int n = in.nextInt();
            int k = in.nextInt();
            int min = n;
            for(int i=1;i<=k;i++){
                int count = n/i;
                if(count*i == n){
                    min = i;
                    break;
                }
            }
            System.out.println(min);
        }
    }
}

    # Calculate the angle of the hour hand
    hour_angle = (H % 12) * 30 + M / 2
    
    # Calculate the angle of the minute hand
    minute_angle = M * 6
    
    # Calculate the angle between the two hands
    angle = abs(hour_angle - minute_angle)
    
    # Calculate the distance between the two hands
    distance = A * math.sin(math.radians(angle)) + B * math.sin(math.radians(180 - angle))
    
    # Print the answer
    print(round(distance, 9))

import sys

n, m = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
a = list(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split()))
segments = []
for i in range(m):
    l, r = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
    segments.append([l, r])

segments.sort()

def get_max_diff(segments, a):
    max_diff = 0
    for i in range(len(segments)):
        l, r = segments[i]
        if l <= a[i] <= r:
            max_diff = max(max_diff, a[i] - min(a[i], r))
    return max_diff

def get_max_diff_with_segments(segments, a):
    max_diff = 0
    for i in range(len(segments)):
        l, r = segments[i]
        if l <= a[i] <= r:
            max_diff = max(max_diff, a[i] - min(a[i], r))
            a[i] = min(a[i], r)
    return max_diff

max_diff = get_max_diff(segments, a)
max_diff_with_segments = get_max_diff_with_segments(segments, a)

print(max_diff)
print(max_diff_with_segments)

for i in range(m):
    l, r = segments[i]
    if l <= a[i] <= r:
        a[i] = min(a[i], r)

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int t = sc.nextInt();
        while(t-->0){
            String s = sc.next();
            int n = s.length();
            int count = 0;
            for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
                if(s.charAt(i)==s.charAt(i+1)){
                    count++;
                }
            }
            System.out.println(count);
        }
    }
}

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] h = new int[n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
            h[i] = sc.nextInt();
        int count = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
            for(int j=i;j<n;j++)
                if(h[i]>h[j])
                    count++;
        System.out.println(count);
    }
}

int main()
{
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    vector<int> p(n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        cin >> p[i];
    }
    sort(p.begin(), p.end());
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        if (p[i] != i + 1)
        {
            int j = p[i] - 1;
            p[i] = j;
            p[j] = i + 1;
        }
    }
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        if (p[i] != i + 1)
        {
            cout << "NO" << endl;
            return 0;
        }
    }
    cout << "YES" << endl;
    return 0;
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= n; j++) {
                if (i * j == n) {
                    int a = i;
                    int b = j;
                    int f = Math.max(Math.log10(a), Math.log10(b));
                    if (f < min) {
                        min = f;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        System.out.println(min);
    }
}

import sys

def main():
    n, m = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
    graph = [[] for _ in range(n)]
    for _ in range(m):
        a, b = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
        graph[a - 1].append(b - 1)
        graph[b - 1].append(a - 1)
    visited = [False] * n
    visited[0] = True
    paths = 0
    stack = [0]
    while stack:
        curr = stack.pop()
        for next in graph[curr]:
            if not visited[next]:
                visited[next] = True
                stack.append(next)
        if all(visited):
            paths += 1
    print(paths)

if __name__ == '__main__':

                min = stamina;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(min);
    }
}

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] arr = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        int max = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                int temp = (arr[i] + arr[j]) / 2;
                if (temp > max) {
                    max = temp;
                }
            }
        }
        System.out.println(max);
    }
}

#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n, a, b;
    cin >> n >> a >> b;
    vector<int> v(n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> v[i];
    }
    sort(v.begin(), v.end());
    int min = v[0] + v[1];
    for (int i = 2; i < n; i++) {
        min = min < v[i] + v[i - 1] ? min : v[i] + v[i - 1];
    }
    cout << min;
    return 0;
}

import sys

n = int(sys.stdin.readline())
x = list(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split()))

def min_max_occupied(x):
    x.sort()
    min_occupied = 0
    max_occupied = 0
    for i in range(1, n):
        if x[i] == x[i-1]:
            continue
        if x[i] == x[i-1] + 1:
            min_occupied += 1
        elif x[i] == x[i-1] - 1:
            max_occupied += 1
    return min_occupied, max_occupied

print(*min_max_occupied(x))

                    count++;
                }
            }
            if (count < min) {
                min = count;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(min);
    }
}

        int n, k;
        int[] arr = new int[n];
        n = sc.nextInt();
        k = sc.nextInt();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int temp = 0;
            for (int j = 0; j < k; j++) {
                temp += Math.abs(arr[i] - j);
            }
            min = Math.min(min, temp);
        }
        System.out.println(min);

}

using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    vector<int> heights;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        int h;
        cin >> h;
        heights.push_back(h);
    }
    sort(heights.begin(), heights.end());
    int count = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (heights[i] == heights[0]) {
            count++;
        }
    }
    cout << count << endl;
    return 0;
}

                    if(i+j+z==s){
                        count++;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        System.out.println(count);
    }
}

def max_points(n, a, b, k, h):
    dp = [[0] * (n + 1) for _ in range(k + 1)]
    for i in range(1, n + 1):
        for j in range(1, k + 1):
            dp[j][i] = max(dp[j][i - 1], dp[j - 1][i - 1] + h[i - 1])
    return dp[k][n]

class Solution:
    def plusOne(self, digits: List[int]) -> List[int]:
        
        # Convert the list of digits to an integer
        num = int(''.join(map(str, digits)))
        
        # Add one to the integer
        num += 1
        
        # Convert the integer back to a list of digits
        digits = list(map(int, str(num)))
        
        return digits

import sys

def gcd(a, b):
    if b == 0:
        return a
    else:
        return gcd(b, a % b)

def main():
    n = int(sys.stdin.readline())
    t = []
    a = []
    for i in range(n):
        t.append(int(sys.stdin.readline()))
        a.append(int(sys.stdin.readline()))
    
    t.sort()
    a.sort()
    
    t_max = t[-1]
    a_max = a[-1]
    
    g = gcd(t_max, a_max)
    
    t_min = t_max // g
    a_min = a_max // g
    
    t_max = t_max - t_min
    a_max = a_max - a_min
    
    t_min = t_min + 1
    a_min = a_min + 1
    
    t_max = t_max * t_min
    a_max = a_max * a_min
    
    print(t_max + a_max)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Fennec {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int k = sc.nextInt();
        int[] h = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            h[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        int count = 0;
        int[] h_copy = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            h_copy[i] = h[i];
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (h_copy[i] > 0) {
                h_copy[i] = 0;
                count++;
            }
        }
        if (count == n) {
            System.out.println(0);
        } else {
            System.out.println(count + k);
        }
    }
}

import sys

def main():
    n, m = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
    edges = []
    for _ in range(m):
        a, b = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
        edges.append((a-1, b-1))
    edges.sort()
    
    visited = [False] * n
    bridges = 0
    for i in range(m):
        if visited[edges[i][0]]:
            continue
        
        visited[edges[i][0]] = True
        visited[edges[i][1]] = True
        
        stack = [edges[i][0]]
        while stack:
            curr = stack.pop()
            for next in edges:
                if next[0] == curr:
                    next[1] = -1
                    stack.append(next[1])
                    break
        
        for next in edges:
            if next[1] == -1:
                bridges += 1
    
    print(bridges)

        while(t-->0){

            int k = sc.nextInt();
            StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder();
            for(int i=0;i<k;i++){
                s.append(sc.next().charAt(0));
            }
            int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

                int count = 0;
                for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                    if(s.charAt(j)==(char)(i+97)){
                        count++;
                    }
                }
                if(count<min){
                    min = count;
                }
            }
            System.out.println(min);
        }
    }
}

            }
        }

This is a dynamic programming problem.
Let's define a function f(i, j) which is the minimum number of moves to make the array good if we start from index i and end at index j.
f(i, j) = min(f(i, k) + f(k+1, j)) for all k in [i, j)

f(i, i) = 0 if i == j
f(i, j) = -1 if i > j

The answer is f(0, n-1).

Explanation:

The map function applies a function to every member of an iterable and returns the result. It takes two parameters: first, the function that is to be applied and secondly, the iterables.
Let's say you are given a list of names, and you have to print a list that contains the length of each name.

>> print (list(map(len, ['Tina', 'Raj', 'Tom'])))  
[4, 3, 3]  

Lambda is a single expression anonymous function often used as an inline function. In simple words, it is a function that has only one line in its body. It proves very handy in functional and GUI programming.

>> sum = lambda a, b, c: a + b + c
>> sum(1, 2, 3)
6

Note:

Lambda functions cannot use the return statement and can only have a single expression. Unlike def, which creates a function and assigns it a name, lambda creates a function and returns the function itself. Lambda can be used inside lists and dictionaries.

import math
import os
import random
import re
import sys

# Complete the symmetricDifference function below.
def symmetricDifference(M, N):
    setM = set(M)
    setN = set(N)
    return sorted(list(setM.symmetric_difference(setN)))

if __name__ == '__main__':
    fptr = open(os.environ['OUTPUT_PATH'], 'w')

    nm = input().split()

    m = int(nm[0])

    n = int(nm[1])

    arr = list(map(int, input().rstrip().split()))

    brr = list(map(int, input().rstrip().split()))

    result = symmetricDifference(arr, brr)

    fptr.write('\n'.join(map(str, result)))
    fptr.write('\n')

    fptr.close()

def cardGameForThree(S_A, S_B, S_C):
    # Write your code here

    # Bob's deck
    bob = list(S_B)
    # Charlie's deck
    charlie = list(S_C)
    # Alice's turn
    while alice:
        # Alice discards the top card in her deck
        alice.pop(0)
        # Alice takes the next turn
        if alice:
            # Alice takes the next turn
            if alice[0] == bob[0] or alice[0] == charlie[0]:
                alice.pop(0)
            else:
                bob.pop(0)
        else:
            # Alice's deck is empty. The game ends and Alice wins the game.

    # Bob's turn
    while bob:
        # Bob discards the top card in his deck
        bob.pop(0)
        # Bob takes the next turn
        if bob:
            # Bob takes the next turn
            if bob[0] == alice[0] or bob[0] == charlie[0]:
                bob.pop(0)
            else:
                alice.pop(0)
        else:
            # Bob's deck is empty. The game ends and Bob wins the game.
            return "B"
    # Charlie's turn
    while charlie:
        # Charlie discards the top card in his deck
        charlie.pop(0)
        # Charlie takes the next turn
        if charlie:
            # Charlie takes the next turn
            if charlie[0] == alice[0] or charlie[0] == bob[0]:
                charlie.pop(0)
            else:
                alice.pop(0)
        else:
            # Charlie's deck is empty. The game ends and Charlie wins the game.
            return "C"

if __name__ == '__main__':

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                int distance = Math.abs(a[i] - a[j]);
                if (distance < min) {
                    min = distance;
                }
            }
        }
        System.out.println(min);
    }
}

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> scc[i];
    }

                ans++;
            }
        }
    }
    cout << ans << endl;
    return 0;
}

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int k = sc.nextInt();
        int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int[] arr = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (arr[i] < min) {
                min = arr[i];
            }
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == min) {
                arr[i] = arr[i] * 2;
            } else {
                arr[i] = arr[i] + k;
            }
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (arr[i] < min) {
                min = arr[i];
            }
        }
        System.out.println(min);
    }
}

"""

import sys

def min_chars(route):
    """
    Returns the minimum number of characters needed to encode the route.
    """
    # Initialize the number of characters to encode the route
    num_chars = 0
    # Initialize the current position
    curr_pos = 0
    # Iterate over the route
    for move in route:
        # If the move is the same as the current position, increment the number of characters
        if move == curr_pos:
            num_chars += 1
        # Otherwise, update the current position
        else:
            curr_pos = move
    # Return the number of characters
    return num_chars

if __name__ == "__main__":
    # Get the input
    input_file = sys.argv[1]
    # Read the input
    with open(input_file, "r") as f:
        # Get the route
        route = f.readline().strip()
    # Print the result
    print(min_chars(route))

# Read the input
read -r -a input

# Translate the input
for i in "${input[@]}"; do
    # Check if the character is in the translation table
    if [[ $i =~ [[:alpha:]] ]]; then
        # Get the index of the character in the translation table
        index=$(echo "${input[@]}" | tr -dc 'a-zA-Z' | grep -o -E '\$[0-9]+')
        # Print the translated character
        echo "${input[$index]}"
    else
        # Print the original character
        echo "$i"
    fi
done

# Print a newline

import math

def min_length(triangles):
    min_length = 0
    for triangle in triangles:
        a, b, c = triangle
        s = (a + b + c) / 2
        area = math.sqrt(s * (s - a) * (s - b) * (s - c))
        min_length = max(min_length, 2 * area / c)
    return min_length

import math

n, p, s, v = map(float, input().split())

def time_to_run_algorithm(n, p, c):
    return n * math.log(n) ** c / p

def time_to_distribute_keys(n, s, v, c):
    return s * (1 + 1 / c) / v

def find_optimal_c(n, p, s, v):
    min_time = float('inf')
    optimal_c = 0
    for c in range(1, n + 1):
        time = time_to_run_algorithm(n, p, c) + time_to_distribute_keys(n, s, v, c)
        if time < min_time:
            min_time = time
            optimal_c = c
    return optimal_c

optimal_c = find_optimal_c(n, p, s, v)
print(time_to_run_algorithm(n, p, optimal_c))
print(time_to_distribute_keys(n, s, v, optimal_c))

    else:

    return sum(s * (4/5)**i for i, s in enumerate(scores)) / 5

def avg_group_score(scores):
    return sum(group_score(scores[:i] + scores[i+1:]) for i in range(len(scores))) / len(scores)

print(avg_group_score(scores))

def judge(instance):
    clauses = instance.split('\n')
    clauses = [clause.split() for clause in clauses]
    clauses = [[int(literal) for literal in clause] for clause in clauses]
    clauses = [[-literal if literal < 0 else literal for literal in clause] for clause in clauses]
    clauses = [[literal if literal > 0 else -literal for literal in clause] for clause in clauses]
    clauses = [[literal if literal != 0 else 0 for literal in clause] for clause in clauses]
    clauses = [tuple(clause) for clause in clauses]
    clauses = set(clauses)
    if len(clauses) < 8:
        return 'unsatisfactory'
    else:
        return 'satisfactory'

instance = input()
print(judge(instance))

import math

def convert_to_roman(num):
    roman_numerals = {
        1000: 'M',
        900: 'CM',
        500: 'D',
        400: 'CD',
        100: 'C',
        90: 'XC',
        50: 'L',
        40: 'XL',
        10: 'X',
        9: 'IX',
        5: 'V',
        4: 'IV',
        1: 'I'
    }
    result = ''
    for value, numeral in roman_numerals.items():
        while num >= value:
            result += numeral
            num -= value
    return result

def convert_to_english(num):
    english_numerals = {
        'M': 1000,
        'CM': 900,
        'D': 500,
        'CD': 400,
        'C': 100,
        'XC': 90,
        'L': 50,
        'XL': 40,
        'X': 10,
        'IX': 9,
        'V': 5,
        'IV': 4,
        'I': 1
    }
    result = 0
    for i in range(len(num)):
        if i > 0 and english_numerals[num[i]] > english_numerals[num[i-1]]:
            result += english_numerals[num[i]] - 2 * english_numerals[num[i-1]]
        else:
            result += english_numerals[num[i]]
    return result

def main():
    num = float(input())
    english_miles = num * 5280
    roman_paces = int(round(1000 * english_miles / 4854))
    print(convert_to_roman(roman_paces))

if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

public class Solution {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] a = new int[n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            a[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        int max = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            int temp = a[i]/a[i+1];
            if(temp>max)
            {
                max = temp;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(max);
    }
}
